{
  "stem": "21626.5",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And so many friendships were renewed and new ones forged and with a little town in Wales, as well.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "You know, it's been a godsend to so many of our lives.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "It's been absolutely wonderful.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "I've got such a wonderful family.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And whether they are in the States, or in Israel, or in the Czech Republic, or here in Britain-- and it doesn't matter if we don't see each other for 40 years or four days.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "We know we can rely on one another.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "It's amazing feeling, this feeling of knowing you will be understood, knowing you would be helped.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "You know, and it really is.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And I think it's because we spent so many extraordinary, extraordinary years together.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And not just that-- I am sharing my life with Harry Steinhauer, with whom I shared a classroom all those years ago.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "He's, again, a Czech Jewish child, originally.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "But unlike me, his parents and sister managed to follow him.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And it's wonderful you know, having this life we have together, this extended family, and the understanding, which I did not have with my husband, because of our completely different backgrounds.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "But more than anything, I got very involved and very much fulfilled when, after 1985, I wrote my autobiography, which is based on the diaries I kept and on all the letters from my parents.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And as I am an author-- I've written books for children and I've worked-- it was a hobby of mine, in translating, also, books from Czech and French into English for various publishers-- I knew that it was a story which was not just mine, but of so many of the children who were here, to a large extent.",
      "word_count": 59
    }
  ],
